data.content:
Use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>()` (MSTest v2+) instead:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()
{
    var service = new UserService();

    Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(
        () => service.CreateUser(null, "John"));
}
```

**Why:** `[ExpectedException]` can't verify *which line* threw, so a bug in setup code could silently pass the test. `Assert.ThrowsException` scopes the assertion to the exact call. You can also inspect the returned exception:

```csharp
var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(
    () => service.CreateUser(null, "John"));

Assert.AreEqual("email", ex.ParamName);
```

For async methods, use `Assert.ThrowsExceptionAsync<T>()`.
